>To add my own two problems:

Ditto:

When pgp is invoked (under Unix) with interrupts/quits/hangups ignored, it
should leave them ignored.  This is standard Unix procedure for processes
that potentially can run in the background, and pgp does very well as a
background process in certain modes (except for this).
